| Form of Governance    | Key Features                                      | Potential Benefits                         | Potential Risks                          |
|----------------------|--------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Noocracy             | Rule by collective intelligence or "hive mind"  | Rational, informed decision-making        | Loss of individual autonomy              |
| Cyberocracy          | Rule by information and AI                        | Rapid, adaptive governance                 | Surveillance, technocratic control       |
| Futarchy             | Vote on values, bet on beliefs (prediction markets) | Data-driven policy selection               | Complexity, separation of values/beliefs |
| Delegative Democracy | Dynamic vote delegation, possibly via AI         | Flexible, personalized representation     | Vote manipulation, coercion risks        |
| Polystate            | Overlapping non-geographic states                 | Freedom to choose governance               | Fragmentation, social division            |
| Seasteading          | Autonomous floating city-states                    | Experimental, libertarian governance       | Legal uncertainty, social isolation       |
| Gerontocracy         | Rule by elders                                    | Stability, experience                      | Ageism, resistance to change              |
| Demarchy             | Randomly selected decision-makers                 | Reduced corruption, increased fairness    | Lack of expertise, accountability issues  |
| Dark Enlightenment   | Neo-reactionary authoritarianism                   | Order, tradition                          | Anti-democratic, elitist                   |
| Post-Apocalyptic     | Tribal, survival-based governance                   | Resilience in crisis                      | Regression, loss of rights                  |

